Former apartheid-era exiles gathered at the Trevor Huddleston Memorial Centre in Sophiatown on Wednesday night to share their memories of working with former African National Congress leader Oliver Reginald Tambo in exile. The event, which is part of South Africa's 100-year anniversary of Tambo's birth, was organised jointly by the UK High Commission, the Oliver and Adelaide Tambo Foundation and the memorial centre. Here are some of the most memorable tales: